# Scenario analysis

## Implied shocks

$$
\begin{aligned}
\hat{\beta}&=(Z^\mathrm{T}WZ)^{-1}Z^\mathrm{T}WX
\end{aligned}
$$


::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
def implied_shocks(shocks, x, z, weights):

    beta = np.linalg.lstsq(np.multiply(weights, z), np.multiply(weights, x), rcond = None)[0]

    result = np.dot(shocks, beta)

    return np.ravel(result)
```
:::

::: {.cell}

